/PGMOTZEY SHABBAT/XX522/XX/PR

/ITThe wine cup is raised./PR

/PR

Behold, my God of help,/PR

in whom I trust, and tremble not./PR

Truly, my strength and melody is Yah, /SCT/XXHE /XXO/XXNE/XX,/PR

who is for me the source of help./PR

So draw, in joy, the waters/PR

from the Fount of Help./PR

All help belongs to You./PR

Upon your people is your blessing. Let it happen!/PR

With us is /SCT/XXHE /XXG/XXREAT /XXO/XXNE/XX of the Multitudes of Heaven,/PR

stronghold for us, the God of Jacob. Be it so!/PR

O, /SCG/XXREAT /XXO/XXNE/XX of the Multitudes of Heaven,/PR

happy is the human being who trusts in you!/PR

/SCR/XXEDEEMING /XXO/XXNE/XX, extend your help./PR

Our sovereign, answer us whenever we may call./PR

The Jews of old had light,/PR

and happiness, and joy, and love--/PR

may it be so for us!/PR

My Cup of Help I raise,/PR

and in /SCT/XXHE /XXO/XXMNIPRESENT/XXòs name/PR

I call./PR

