Biblical references include Isaiah 12:2-3; Psalms 3:9, 46:12, 84:13, 20:10;
Esther 8:16; Psalm 116:13./PR

/PR

/SCK/XXAVANAH/XX. Tradition has it that the /ITneshamah yeterah/XX / additional soul we
receive at the beginning of Shabbat stays with us until /ITHavdalah/XX, when it
departs. We do not want to lose that additional bit of soul, and therefore
linger and relish the fading embers of the day.    /SC/XXD.A.T./XX/PR

